\section{Introduction: The Traveler Defined}

Let a \textbf{human traveler} be an agent moving through a space of musical features. The traveler has:

\begin{itemize}
    \item Perceptual state $\mathbf{P}(t) \in \mathbb{R}^5$
    \item Memory $\mathbf{M}(t) \in \mathbb{R}^5$
    \item Attention $\alpha(t) \in [0,1]$
    \item Fatigue $\phi(t) \in [0,1]$
    \item Preference vector $\mathbf{w}(t) \in \mathbb{R}^5$
    \item Uncapturable emotion $\mathcal{E}(t) \in [0,10]$
\end{itemize}

\section{Feature Space: The Coordinates of Post-Punk}

Each song is represented by a 5-dimensional feature vector:

\[
\mathbf{T} = \big( S,\; H,\; \sigma_c,\; R,\; C_v \big) \in \mathbb{R}^5
\]

where:

\[
\begin{aligned}
S &= \frac{\sum_{i \in \text{offbeat}} O_i}{\sum_{j \in \text{onbeat}} O_j} \quad &\text{(Syncopation index)} \\
H &= -\sum_{s} p(s) \log_2 p(s) \quad &\text{(IOI entropy)} \\
\sigma_c &= \text{std}\big( \mu_{\text{spectral}}(t) \big) \quad &\text{(Spectral centroid variability)} \\
R &= \sum_{t} \sum_{i<j} w_{ij} \cdot C_i(t) C_j(t) \quad &\text{(Harmonic roughness)} \\
C_v &= \frac{\text{std}(\text{tempo}(t))}{\text{mean}(\text{tempo}(t))} \quad &\text{(Tempo stability)}
\end{aligned}
\]

